detour_name: Gippsland line - coaches replacing trains (26-28 October)
detour_description:
Friday 26 October

From Southern Cross:
The 18.34 service from Southern Cross Station to Bairnsdale will run as a train to Traralgon, connecting with coaches from Traralgon to Bairnsdale.

The 23.01 and 23.25 trains from Southern Cross Station to Traralgon will be replaced by coaches between Melbourne and Pakenham, connecting with trains to Traralgon.

Saturday 27 October and Sunday 28 October

Coaches will replace Traralgon, Sale and Bairnsdale trains between Southern Cross Station and Pakenham, connecting with trains between Pakenham and Traralgon, Sale and Bairnsdale

Bairnsdale, Stratford, Rosedale and Sale customers
Some Bairnsdale trains will be replaced by coaches for the entire journey for Bairnsdale, Stratford, Rosedale and Sale customers.

From Southern Cross:
The 18.16 train from Southern Cross Station to Bairnsdale will be replaced by coaches running express to Rosedale then will stop at Sale, Stratford and Bairnsdale.

From Bairnsdale:
The 6.28 Saturday and 7.41 Sunday trains from Bairnsdale to Southern Cross Station will be replaced by coaches stopping all stations to Traralgon then dropping off customers as required to Melbourne.

General Information  

  • There is limited space for bikes on V/Line trains and coach replacement services.
  • No pets or hot food allowed on replacement coaches.
  • Customers require a valid myki or paper ticket to travel on all V/Line replacement coach services. Please touch on and touch off your myki to ensure you pay the correct fare.
  • In Melbourne, coaches will arrive and depart from:
    • The Southern Cross Station coach terminal located on Spencer Street, opposite Little Bourke Street;
    • Flinders Street Station on Flinders Street opposite Degraves Street.
  • Coaches will not stop at Clayton Station. Customers should take a Metro service to and from Dandenong.
  • Coaches do not stop at Richmond Station. Customers should take a Metro service to and from Southern Cross Station or Caulfield.
  • Customers travelling solely between Pakenham and Melbourne may travel on V/Line coach replacement services where space is available once customers connecting with train services have boarded.
  • Customers requiring special assistance please call 1800 800 007 before travelling.

detour_name: Gippsland line - coaches replacing trains (18-21 November 2018)
detour_description:
Sunday 18 November
 
From Southern Cross: 
The 21:35 train from Southern Cross Station to Traralgon will be replaced by coaches for the entire journey.
 
Monday 19 November to Wednesday 21 November:

From Traralgon:
The 18:51, 19:45 and 20:21 services from Traralgon to Southern Cross Station will run as  trains to Pakenham, connecting with coaches from Pakenham to Melbourne.

From Bairnsdale:
The 18:18 service from Bairnsdale to Southern Cross Station will run as a train to Pakenham, connecting with coaches from Pakenham to Melbourne.

From Southern Cross:
The 20:34, 21:54, 23:01 and 23:59 trains from Southern Cross Station to Traralgon will be replaced by coaches from Melbourne to Pakenham, connecting with trains from Pakenham to Traralgon.
 
General Information 

  • There is limited space for bikes on V/Line trains and coach replacement services.
  • No pets or hot food/liquids allowed on replacement coaches.
  • Customers require a valid myki or paper ticket to travel on all V/Line replacement coach services. Please touch on and touch off your myki to ensure you pay the correct fare.
  • In Melbourne, coaches will arrive and depart from:
    • the Southern Cross Station coach terminal located on Spencer Street, opposite Little Bourke Street;
    • Flinders Street Station on Flinders Street opposite Degraves Street.
  • Coaches will not stop at Clayton Station. Customers should take a Metro service to and from Dandenong.
  • Coaches do not stop at Richmond Station. Customers should take a Metro service to and from Southern Cross Station or Caulfield.
  • Customers requiring special assistance please call 1800 800 007 before travelling.

name: Cranbourne and Pakenham lines – buses replacing trains
location: Multiple stations affected
description: Buses replacing trains on sections of the Cranbourne and Pakenham lines from Saturday 1 December to Sunday 23 December. During this time, free travel will be offered to passengers on disrupted sections of the Cranbourne and Pakenham and Gippsland lines due to major works.
detour_description:
Detailed information and timetables can be found at ptv.vic.gov.au.

1-2 December

Buses replacing trains from first service on Saturday 1 December to 5pm on Sunday 2 December, between Westall, Cranbourne and Pakenham stations.

2-3 December

Buses replacing trains from 5pm to last service on Sunday 2 December between Caulfield, Cranbourne and Pakenham stations.

3-15 December

Buses replacing trains from the first service on Monday 3 December to 4am on Saturday 15 December, between Westall, Cranbourne and Pakenham stations.

15-16 December

Buses replacing trains from 4am on Saturday 15 December to last service on Sunday 16 December, between Dandenong, Cranbourne and Pakenham stations.

17-23 December

Buses replacing trains from first service on Monday 17 December to Sunday 23 December, between Dandenong and Pakenham (Cranbourne services reinstated).

20-21 December

Buses replacing trains from 7pm on Thursday 20 December between Dandenong and Cranbourne stations.

21-22 December

Buses replacing trains from 11.30pm to 4am each night on Friday 21 December, Saturday 22 December and Sunday 23 December, between Dandenong and Cranbourne stations.
